# RTO & RPO — the only two numbers

Resilience reduces to two numbers, quoted **per workload**:

- **RTO** — *Recovery Time* — how long you can be **down**
- **RPO** — *Recovery Point* — how much **data** you can lose (time to last good copy)

## Per workload, not per company

| Workload | RTO | RPO |
|---|---|---|
| **Checkout** | < 5 min | < 30 s |
| **Reporting warehouse** | 24 h | 4 h |

Every choice — sync vs. async, Multi-AZ vs. multi-region, hot vs. cold — **pays for a smaller RTO/RPO**.

## Two costs scale as you tighten

- **Money** — replicas, cross-region bandwidth
- **Complexity** — failover automation, drift, testing

*How small is small enough?* — the rest of this module is the levers.
